@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Template Home";
}

<main class="space-y-8">
    <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="templateTitle">
        <h1 id="templateTitle" class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Welcome to ASP.NET + Vite</h1>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            A starter template for building classic ASP.NET MVC/Web API applications on <strong>.NET Framework 4.8.1</strong> while using a modern frontend build pipeline.
            Use this page as a launchpad for your own landing, admin, or enterprise dashboard workflow.
            Current stack includes <strong>Vite 8.0.1</strong>, <strong>Tailwind CSS 4.2</strong>, and <strong>Lucide</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Security-conscious defaults are enabled out of the box, with nonce-based CSP handling and centralized asset registration.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/aspnet/mvc/overview" class="rounded-md border border-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-slate-900 transition hover:bg-slate-50 dark:border-slate-700 dark:text-slate-100 dark:hover:bg-slate-800">
                ASP.NET MVC Docs
            </a>
            <a href="@Url.Action("About", "Home")" class="rounded-md bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:bg-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-100 dark:text-slate-900 dark:hover:bg-white">
                View About Page
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900">
            <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">New template features</h2>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                <li><strong>Modular frontend entry:</strong> <code>Scripts/app.js</code> now orchestrates layout modules in <code>Scripts/layout/</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Icons:</strong> Lucide-based icon swap using Tailwind classes for theme/menu buttons.</li>
                <li><strong>Security:</strong> Global nonce-based <code>Content-Security-Policy</code> filter with <code>Helpers/NonceHelper.cs</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Assets:</strong> <code>wwwroot/dist</code> output via Vite manifest in production.</li>
                <li><strong>Vite integration:</strong> <code>@Html.Vite("Styles/app.css", "Scripts/app.js")</code></li>
                <li>Build output folder: <code>wwwroot/dist</code></li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900">
            <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Quick start</h2>
            <ol class="list-inside list-decimal space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                <li>Run <code>npm install</code></li>
                <li>Run <code>npm run dev</code> for local development</li>
                <li>Run <code>npm run build</code> for production assets</li>
                <li>Update <code>Views/Home/Index.cshtml</code> to match your own content model</li>
                <li>Press F5 in Visual Studio</li>
            </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900">
            <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Recommended next edits</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                Update navigation and page features from the new modules:
                <span class="font-medium">Scripts/layout/theme.js</span> for theme state logic and
                <span class="font-medium">Scripts/layout/menu.js</span> for mobile menu behavior.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                <li>Replace placeholder sections with your own domain content.</li>
                <li>Move reusable fragments into <code>Views/Shared</code> partials.</li>
                <li>Hook API-backed data into the existing card layout.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-xl border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 p-4 dark:border-blue-900 dark:bg-blue-950">
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-200">
            To customize this landing page, edit <code>Views/Home/Index.cshtml</code>.
            To customize styles, update <code>Styles/app.css</code>.
            For UI behavior, update <code>Scripts/app.js</code> or its modules in <code>Scripts/layout/</code>.
            For CSP helpers, review <code>Filters/ContentSecurityPolicyFilter.cs</code> and <code>Helpers/NonceHelper.cs</code>.
        </p>
    </section>

</main>